            "filePath": "/Users/roklenarcic/clojure-projects/memento/doc/scoped-caching.md",
            "newString": "\nMemento's `with-caches` macro temporarily replaces caches for tagged functions:\n\n```clojure\n(require '[memento.core :as m]\n         '[memento.config :as mc])\n\n;; Tag functions that should have request-scoped caching\n(m/defmemo get-user\n  {mc/type mc/caffeine\n   mc/tags [:request]}\n  [user-id]\n  (db/fetch-user user-id))\n\n(m/defmemo get-user-orders\n  {mc/type mc/caffeine\n   mc/tags [:request]}\n  [user-id]\n  (db/fetch-orders user-id))\n\n;; In your request handling\n(m/with-caches :request\n  (constantly (m/create {mc/type mc/caffeine}))  ; Factory that creates a fresh cache\n  (handle-request request))\n```\n\nInside `with-caches`:\n- All `:request`-tagged functions use a fresh cache\n- The cache is discarded when the block exits\n- Functions called with the same arguments within the block hit the cache\n\n## Ring Middleware Pattern\n\nWrap your Ring handler to provide request-scoped caching:\n\n```clojure\n(defn wrap-request-cache [handler]\n  (fn [request]\n    (m/with-caches :request\n      (constantly (m/create {mc/type mc/caffeine}))\n      (handler request))))\n\n;; Apply to your app\n(def app\n  (-> handler\n      wrap-request-cache\n      wrap-params\n      wrap-session))\n```\n\nNow all `:request`-tagged cached functions automatically get a fresh cache per request.\n\n## Consulting Long-Term Caches\n\nOften you want request-scoped caching but also want to benefit from a long-term cache. Use `m/consulting`:\n\n```clojure\n;; Long-term cache for users (1 hour TTL)\n(def user-cache (m/create {mc/type mc/caffeine mc/ttl [1 :h] mc/size< 10000}))\n\n(m/defmemo get-user\n  {mc/type mc/caffeine\n   mc/tags [:request]}\n  [user-id]\n  (db/fetch-user user-id))\n\n;; Bind to the long-term cache by default\n(m/bind #'get-user {} user-cache)\n\n;; Middleware that consults the long-term cache\n(defn wrap-request-cache [handler]\n  (fn [request]\n    (m/with-caches :request\n      (fn [existing-cache]\n        ;; Create a request cache that CONSULTS the long-term cache\n        (m/create (m/consulting {mc/type mc/caffeine} existing-cache)))\n      (handler request))))\n```\n\nWith `consulting`:\n- Cache **hits** check request cache first, then long-term cache\n- Cache **misses** fetch data and store in request cache only\n- Long-term cache is **not modified** by request-scoped operations\n\nThis is the recommended pattern for most web applications.\n\n## Multiple Scope Tags\n\nYou can have multiple scope levels:\n\n```clojure\n(m/defmemo get-user\n  {mc/type mc/caffeine\n   mc/tags [:request :user]}  ; Participates in both scopes\n  [user-id]\n  (db/fetch-user user-id))\n\n;; Outer scope for long-running operations\n(m/with-caches :user\n  (constantly (m/create {mc/type mc/caffeine mc/ttl [5 :m]}))\n  \n  ;; Inner scope for each request\n  (m/with-caches :request\n    (constantly (m/create {mc/type mc/caffeine}))",
